Vice President Biden expressed his sadness over the passing of Ambassador Max M. Kampelman and described him as an accomplished and decent man. He highlighted Max's career in law, politics, and diplomacy, where he provided advice and wisdom to both Democrats and Republicans for over six decades. During the Cold War, Max played a key role in negotiating important agreements on human rights and nuclear arms reductions. In his later years, he dedicated himself to advocating for a world without nuclear weapons, aligning with the vision of Ronald Reagan and others. Vice President Biden extended his condolences to Max's family.